ub.io/publication/nalmpantis-2023-hierarchical/</link><pubDate>Sun, 03 Dec 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/publication/nalmpantis-2023-hierarchical/</guid><description/></item><item><title>UAI Spotlight Talk: BISCUIT - Causal Representation Learning from Binary Interactions</title><link>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/uai-spotlight-talk-biscuit-causal-representation-learning-from-binary-interactions/</link><pubDate>Thu, 03 Aug 2023 12:10:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/uai-spotlight-talk-biscuit-causal-representation-learning-from-binary-interactions/</guid><description/></item><item><title>BISCUIT - Causal Representation Learning from Binary Interactions</title><link>https://phlippe.github.io/post/biscuit/</link><pubDate>Wed, 21 Jun 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/post/biscuit/</guid><description>&lt;p>Check out our project page: &lt;a href="https://phlippe.github.io/BISCUIT/">&lt;a href="https://phlippe.github.io/BISCUIT/">https://phlippe.github.io/BISCUIT/&lt;/a>&lt;/a>!&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Abstract&lt;/strong>: Identifying the causal variables of an environment and how to intervene on them is of core value in applications such as robotics and embodied AI. While an agent can commonly interact with the environment and may implicitly perturb the behavior of some of these causal variables, often the targets it affects remain unknown. In this paper, we show that causal variables can still be identified for many common setups, e.g., additive Gaussian noise models, if the agent&amp;rsquo;s interactions with a causal variable can be described by an unknown binary variable. This happens when each causal variable has two different mechanisms, e.g., an observational and an interventional one. Using this identifiability result, we propose BISCUIT, a method for simultaneously learning causal variables and their corresponding binary interaction variables. On three robotic-inspired datasets, BISCUIT accurately identifies causal variables and can even be scaled to complex, realistic environments for embodied AI.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>BISCUIT - Causal Representation Learning from Binary Interactions</title><link>https://phlippe.github.io/publication/lippe-2023-biscuit/</link><pubDate>Thu, 15 Jun 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/publication/lippe-2023-biscuit/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Causal Representation Learning for Instantaneous and Temporal Effects in Interactive Systems</title><link>https://phlippe.github.io/publication/lippe-2022-icitris/</link><pubDate>Fri, 24 Feb 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/publication/lippe-2022-icitris/</guid><description/></item><item><title>KAUST Rising Stars in AI: Causal Representation Learning</title><link>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/kaust-rising-stars-in-ai-causal-representation-learning/</link><pubDate>Sun, 19 Feb 2023 15:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/kaust-rising-stars-in-ai-causal-representation-learning/</guid><description/></item><item><title>ICAI Meetup: CITRIS - Causal Identifiability from Temporal Intervened Sequences</title><link>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/icai-meetup-citris-causal-identifiability-from-temporal-intervened-sequences/</link><pubDate>Thu, 06 Oct 2022 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/icai-meetup-citris-causal-identifiability-from-temporal-intervened-sequences/</guid><description/></item><item><title>CI Working Group: Learning Causal Variables from Temporal Observations</title><link>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/ci-working-group-learning-causal-variables-from-temporal-observations/</link><pubDate>Tue, 04 Oct 2022 17:30:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/ci-working-group-learning-causal-variables-from-temporal-observations/</guid><description/></item><item><title>UAI Invited Talk: Learning Causal Variables from Temporal Sequences with Interventions</title><link>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/uai-invited-talk-learning-causal-variables-from-temporal-sequences-with-interventions/</link><pubDate>Fri, 05 Aug 2022 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/uai-invited-talk-learning-causal-variables-from-temporal-sequences-with-interventions/</guid><description/></item><item><title>ICML Spotlight: CITRIS - Causal Identifiability from Temporal Intervened Sequences</title><link>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/icml-spotlight-citris-causal-identifiability-from-temporal-intervened-sequences/</link><pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2022 15:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/talk/icml-spotlight-citris-causal-identifiability-from-temporal-intervened-sequences/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Intervention Design for Causal Representation Learning</title><link>https://phlippe.github.io/publication/lippe-2022-intervention/</link><pubDate>Thu, 14 Jul 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://phlippe.github.io/publication/lippe-2022-intervention/</guid><description/></item><